    <description>DBA-inspired miniature rules specifically designed for use with 2mm scale Napoleonic figure blocks, to be played on a 2 foot by 2 foot (2' x 2')table. Players build up units of soldiers by expending Army Points (AP), and typically fight engagements with 40 AP of units aside. The turn sequence is the familiar structure of:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Player 1 moves&amp;#10;Player 1 rallies&amp;#10;Player 2 shoots, cavalry countercharges&amp;#10;Player 1 melees&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Then the reverse: &amp;#10;Player 2 moves&amp;#10;Player 2 rallies&amp;#10;Player 1 shoots, cavalry countercharges&amp;#10;Player 2 melees&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each unit represents a regiment and each player controls the equivalent of a corps of soldiers. Ground scale is 1&amp;quot; = 400 paces, or &amp;frac14;&amp;quot; = 100 paces. Figures should be mounted on 1&amp;quot; x &amp;frac12;&amp;quot; bases, representing about 1200 men. All units move in increments of &amp;frac34;&amp;quot; or 300 paces.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Combat is resolved by a single die roll, with a long list of possibly applicable modifiers. Results are of the variety of Disrupted, Recoil, or Destroyed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Six-sided dice and a ruler (marked in &amp;frac34;&amp;quot; or 300 pace increments) are required to play.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
